THE two Ukhozi FM producers who were suspended have been rescheduled. Vuka Africa breakfast show technical producer Mandla “Njinji” Magwaza and content producer Babheke Mthethwa are back at work. But DJ Sgqemeza is still silenced and serving his punishment at home and will be back on air on 20 June. The three, who have now survived the chop, were suspended two weeks ago for allegedly playing an unauthorised song from one of their cellphones that was not on the breakfast show’splaylist. A source inside Ukhozi FM told Daily Sun the station was tough on DJ Sgqemeza because he had been working for the station for many years, and was expected to know better and not break the rules. ALSO READ: Musa Mseleku can't believe his luck with MaCele! The source said that’s why Mandla and Babheke got minor punishment and were back on duty on Ukhozi FM Top 20 on Saturday, 28 May. Mandla is the presenter and Babheke is the content producer. “The trio was warned to not break the rules again.” The source added that Ukhozi FM is making sure that there is no presenter or producer who is above the station. SABC group executive corporate affairs Gugu Ntuli confirmed that Mandla and Babheke were rescheduled from 25 May. “Sipho Mbatha will be back on air on 20 June. “The SABC does not discuss employer and employee matters in the public domain,” she said.